<HEADLINE> Urban Poor Development Project Starts in Phnom Penh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 20 (Xinhua) -- A new housing project -- the
Phnom Penh Urban Poor Communities and Municipality Development
Project, started Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Hun Sen, government officials, representatives
of international organizations and non-government organizations,
as well as diplomats attended an inauguration ceremony held at the
Meanchey Development Community near Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
After expressing his support to the project, Hun Sen promised
that the government will appropriate money to buy 10 hectares of
land for the urban poor for resettlement. Meanwhile, the prime
minister urged the international community to offer financial
assistance to the project.
</P>
<P>
The project received technical and financially assistance from
the United Nations Development Programs (UNDP), the United Nations
Center for Human Settlements (UNHCS), and the U.K. Department for
International Development (U.K.-DFID).
</P>
<P>
In the past years, the municipality has relocated about 1,123
families of urban poor from difference squatters. Phnom Penh
Municipality is also preparing to move 1,794 families living on
riverside to the new location. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
