<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Telecom Workers End Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 8,000 Zimbabwean posts
and telecommunication workers on Thursday ended their three-day
national strike.
</P>
<P>
They went on strike on Monday to protest over proposed salary
cuts after an error in awarding the increments in February.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Workers' Union of the Posts and
Telecommunications Corporation Lovemore Matombo said the workers
agreed to go back to work and start negotiating for a new salary
structure.
</P>
<P>
He said the workers would this month get their salaries on the
old scale effected in January while a new salary structure is
being worked out.
</P>
<P>
In the past three days, the striking workers closed all offices
of the posts and telecommunications in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
