<HEADLINE> Jiang's Visit a Milestone: Greek President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Greek President Costis
Stephanopoulos described Chinese President Jiang Zemin's current
Greece visit as an "important milestone" in the development of the
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The people of the two countries are full of confident in the
further development of the bilateral relations in the 21st century,
he said at a banquet he hosted in Jiang's honor.
</P>
<P>
Extending his warm welcome to Jiang, Stephanopoulos expressed
his appreciation for China's progress in the construction of China
and its important role in the international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said that although the bilateral relations have enjoyed
stable progress since the diplomatic ties were forged in 1972,
there is still great potential to tap in the economic cooperation
and trade between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The sound political relations have laid solid foundation for
the economic cooperation between the two countries, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Greece's upcoming admission to European Economic and Monetary
Union will create more favorable conditions for the Greece-China
cooperation, the president said.
</P>
<P>
Greece hopes that the relations between the European Union and
China will keep on improving and advancing, he said, adding his
country hopes that China will enter into the World Trade
Organization at an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of China's One China, Two Systems principle,
and reiterated that Greece will adhere to the one China policy and
hopes that the Taiwan problem will be resolved peacefully.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived here earlier the day for a state visit at the
invitation of Stephanopoulos. This is first visit to Greece by a
Chinese head of state, and also the fourth leg of Jiang's five-
nation tour of Asia, Europe and Africa, which has brought him to
Israel, Palestine and Turkey, and will take him to South Africa.
Furthermore, President Jiang also meet with Egyptian President
Hosni Mubarak in Alexandria City of Egypt. 
</P>
