<HEADLINE> France's Renault Reaches Alliance Agreement With S.Korea Samsung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- France's Renault automobile
corporation confirmed on Friday that it has reached an agreement
with South Korea's Samsung Motors on resuming and financing the
latter's auto production.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of Renault said that his company and its creditors
will sign an agreement on financing the project next Monday in
Paris.
</P>
<P>
Renault and Samsung struck the agreement on Friday after
holding exclusive talks since January on reviving the activities
of Samsung Motors, which is burdened with a 3.7 billion U.S.
dollar debt as a result of the collapse of its activities amid the
Asian economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Samsung announced earlier on Friday that a ceremony on the
alliance will be held next Thursday or Friday in Pusan, where
Samsung Motors is based, with the participation of representatives
from Renault and its creditors.
</P>
<P>
Renault will be the first foreign automaker to take over a part
of the South Korean auto market, considered to be very closed to
outsiders.
</P>
<P>
The French automaker estimates that it will share from 10 to 15
percent of the auto market in South Korea after allying with
Samsung.
</P>
<P>
Renault has already set up an alliance with the Japanese
automaker Nissan. 
</P>
