<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Greek Presidents Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here Friday that China would like to join hands with Greece to
push the bilateral cooperation to a new high in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
There are great potential and bright prospect for the
cooperation because the two countries share similar views on many
international issues, Jiang said during his talks with Greek
President Costis Stephanopoulos.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived here earlier the day for a state visit at the
invitation of Stephanopoulos. This is first visit to Greece by a
Chinese head of state.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President told his Greek counterpart that he was
very pleased to have the opportunity to pay the visit to Greece,
and he will pay his respects to the relics of the Greek
civilization and acquaint himself with the progress the Greek
people have made in the construction of the country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his satisfaction with the development of the
Sino-Greek relations, saying that the two countries have
positively promote the exchanges and cooperation in various fields
since the diplomatic ties were forged 28 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The principles of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit
have been applied in such cooperation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Touching upon the two way trade, Jiang said that China always
treasures its economic cooperation with Greece, which has a bright
future.
</P>
<P>
Recent years have witness remarkable growth of the trade volume
between the two countries and China has made efforts to maintain
the balanced and constant growth of the bilateral economic
cooperation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Chinese government's strategy of developing
its western region on a massive scale offers lots of cooperation
opportunities for Chinese and foreign businesses including those
in Greece.
</P>
<P>
China would like to push forward its trade ties with Greece
together with the European country by exploring new field of the
cooperation, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his appreciation for the Sino-Greek cultural
cooperation, saying that the two countries should cement such
cooperation by bringing into full play the cultural resources of
the two ancient countries.
</P>
<P>
"China adopts positive attitude towards such cooperation," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Stephanopoulos extended his warm welcome to Jiang. He said that
Jiang's visit is of great significance to the development of the
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The two countries do not only have long history, but share same
views on many world affairs, he said, adding that there are great
potential to tap in the Greece-China cooperation in many sectors.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the great achievement China has made and
expressed his hope that the economic development of China will
create more opportunities for the bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Greek president stressed that his country will adhere to
the one China policy and appreciate China's One Country, Two
Systems principle adopted in its reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciation for Greek's stance on the
Taiwan issue. He also asked his Greek counterpart to visit China
at his convenient time.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, the two heads of states also exchanged views
on situations in the Balkan region and Kosovo issue. They agreed
that the two countries take similar stance on the matter because
both of them hold that the problem should be resolved by
implementing the relevant resolutions of the UN Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Stephanopoulos also reached the consensus that the
two countries should strengthen exchanges of views and
consultation on the international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Greece is the fourth leg of Jiang's five-nation tour of Asia,
Europe and Africa, which has brought him to Israel, Palestine and
Turkey, and will take him to South Africa. Furthermore, President
Jiang also met with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in Alexandria
City of Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
