<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Taiwan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here Friday that China is always committed to the peaceful
resolving of the Taiwan issue, but the One China principle is the
prerequisite of the peaceful reunification of the country.
</P>
<P>
"We would like to exchange views on the relations across the
Taiwan Straits and peaceful reunification with all parties,
organizations and personnel in Taiwan which support the One China
Principle," Jiang said. "However, we will never tolerate any form
of the Taiwan independence."
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during his meeting with Greek Prime
Minister Constantinos Simitis the afternoon of the day.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the Chinese government is listening to what
the new leaders in Taiwan say and observing what they do.
</P>
<P>
"Our fundamental principle is that only after the One China
Principle is recognized, are the relations across the Taiwan
Straits able to advance healthily," he added.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his conviction that as the One China, Two Systems
policy has been successfully adopted in Hong Kong and Macao, the
Taiwan issue can be settled at an early date through the
implementation of the policy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is here for a state visit to Greece at the invitation of
Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos. This is first visit to
Greece by a Chinese head of state, and also the fourth leg of
Jiang's five-nation tour of Asia, Europe and Africa, which has
brought him to Israel, Palestine and Turkey, and will take him to
South Africa. Furthermore, President Jiang also meet with Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak in Alexandria City of Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
