<HEADLINE> French Air Force to Conduct Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The French Air Force will conduct
from April 25 till May 12 an exercise with the participation of
nine allied countries and NATO, said the French military
authorities on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the exercise is to train all the units and
organs of the air force in the execution of their missions in
conventional operations with a real scenario, said the Information
Service of Public Relations of the French Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
The air forces from the United Arab Emirates, Singapore, Spain,
Italy Turkey, Morocco, Britain and Germany, as well as some units
from NATO, will join the exercise, which will involve 150 aircraft,
including 125 fighters.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six other countries will send observers to the exercise,
which will be commanded by General Jean Brevot, who is in charge
of air defense and air operations of the French air force, as well
as a European air group consisting of six European states. 
</P>
