<HEADLINE> Greece React Swifly to Criticism from Samaranch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Greece reacted swiftly on Friday
to criticism from Juan Antonio Samaranch, president of the
International Olympic Committee(IOC), over delays in  the
preparations for the 2004 Athens Games, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch warned on Thursday in Lausanne that the Games could
be endangered if the Greeks failed to improve their organisation
drastically by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
One organiser said Samaranch's statement could be just what
was needed.
</P>
<P>
