realise what needs to be done," the organiser was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Sources on the Athens 2004 organising committee said the IOC
has long been concerned about the slow progress of several
projects, including the construction of an Olympic village,hotel
accommodation and transport to venues.
</P>
<P>
Greece's notorious bureaucracy, in-fighting among the many
officials in charge of the Games and legal complications in taking
even minor decisions have caused delays that prompted some Greek
officials to describe the past two years as wasted, reports said.
</P>
