<HEADLINE> Nor'wester Kills 9, Injures over 100 in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- At least nine people, including two
women and four children were killed and over 100 others injured as
a Nor'wester with a speed of 120 kph lashed four upazilas (sub-
districts) in Netrokona, some 160 kilometers north to Dhaka,
leveling 2,000 houses Thursday night, the official Bangladesh News
Agency reported here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Commissioner of Netrakona Mohammad Quddus Khan said that
the Nor'wester with wind speed ranging from 92 kph to 120 kph
caused widespread damage.
</P>
<P>
He said the disaster that lasted for nearly 45 minutes left a
trail of devastation and at least 2,000 tin-shed houses were
flattened, forcing the victims to sleep in the open.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said all the deaths were due to house collapse.
</P>
<P>
Over a dozen educational and religious institutions were also
damaged. Hundreds of trees were uprooted while electric and
telephone poles were also damaged.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers said the deputy commissioner visited different
parts of worst-hit upazila. They said 10 metric tons of food aid
were sent to the affected upazilas as emergency relief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
