<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals to Cambodia Rise in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in the first
quarter of this year in Cambodia rose year-on-year by 47.63
percent, according to figures of the Tourism Ministry Friday.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia received 91,840 tourists compared with 62,209 in the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The arrivals in January recorded a 38.5 percent increase while
February and March recorded 69.23 and 37.64 percent increases
respectively. The largest arrivals to Cambodia in the first
quarter of this year came from the United States at 8,632,
followed by France 7,565, China 7,1 14 and Japan 7,028.
</P>
<P>
Tourists from the Asia-Pacific region topped the list, making
up 56.88 percent of the visitors.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the 'open skies' policy adopted by the Royal
Government of Cambodia, the tourists flew directly from Bangkok to
Siem Reap has recorded a 316.25 percent increase in the first
quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Some foreign airlines have already taken the advantage of the
policy and introduced direct flights to Siem Reap. Besides Royal
AirCambodge, other airlines serving Siem Reap include Vietnam
Airlines and Bangkok Airways.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shanghai and Singapore Airlines are also considering
direct flights.
</P>
<P>
More than 367,000 tourists visited Cambodia last year, an
increase of 28.35 percent over 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
