<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Passes Code For Citizens Who Risk Their Lives For A Just Cause </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The legislative body in Beijing
today passed a code that awards citizens who risk their lives for
others or engaged in brave deeds for the good of the Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
The law highlights a question which has been debated in the
last couple of years: Should deeds be rewarded by handing out
money? The mass media reports again and again of crimes committed
in public while bystanders do nothing. Those who do confront
criminals are often ridiculed. "We hope the law will help to
maintain a just society through legal means," said Huang Zhimin,
the spokesman of the Standing Committee of the Beijing Municipal
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
According to him, since a draft form of the law first appeared
in local newspapers to solicit advice from the public, more than 6,
000 pieces of suggestions and advices have been collected.
</P>
<P>
The new law will go into effect from August 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
