<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Faulty Fire Control Systems Repaired In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Officials with Beijing Fire
Prevention Bureau said today that leaks in the fire control
systems, which might cause fire, have been repaired in
recreational areas.
</P>
<P>
During a 17 day inspection, which started on April 3, about 4,
000 staff members from the Bureau checked about 6,000 places in
the city. About 725 places were ordered to improve their fire
control equipment.
</P>
<P>
Serious leaks of fire control system were found in about 58
venues. They have been ordered to suspend their business
operations until their problems are fixed. Operators from another
145 venues have been fined.
</P>
<P>
In the past few months, several fires broke out in Henan,
Guangdong, Jilin, and other provinces, arousing public concern.
</P>
</TEXT>
