<HEADLINE> Tibet Sets Goals for Developing China's Western Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Region has
worked out major objectives for the implementation of the
government's initiated strategy to develop the western parts of
China.
</P>
<P>
Vice-chairman of the regional government Chen Chuantang told a
news conference today that Tibet will raise its economic and
social development level as well as the living standards of the
people with the goals of realizing modernization in 50 years along
with the rest of China.
</P>
<P>
The region will be built into a world-famous tourism resort,
the largest bio-engineering resources center in China, green food
research and development base, Tibetan medicine production and and
export center, as well as a rare metals base.
</P>
<P>
To achieve those goals, Tibet should speed up infrastructure
construction, restructure its industrial mix, seek sustainable
development, develop science and technology and train talented
young people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
