<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Meets with Congolese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Mayor Liu Qi said here
today that Beijing would, in its power, help with the
reconstruction of Brazzaville, capital of the Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
Liu made the remark while meeting with a delegation of the
Brazzaville City Government led by Brazzaville city Mayor Benoit
Moundele Ngollo
</P>
<P>
Beijing and Brazzaville have maintained their friendship for
years, Liu said, adding that given your city has difficulties in
its reconstruction, the Beijing Municipal People's Government will
assist in its power, and will also encourage State and private
businesses to join the reconstruction effort of Brazzaville.
</P>
<P>
Ngollo thanked Beijing and expressed the hope for furthering
the friendly relations between the two cities.
</P>
<P>
Ngollo and his party, who arrived in Beijing Thursday, are here
as guests of the Beijing city government.  
