<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 21 (Xinhua) -- An apartment blast in Brovary just
outside the Ukrainian capital Kiev may have been caused by a bomb,
Interfax-Ukraine quoted investigators as saying on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's blast in a nine-story apartment block killed three
people and injured five others. The explosion in the stairwell
sent rafters slamming through seven floors of the building.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry Friday denied rumors that the building was
hit by a test-fired missile that veered off course.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said only one surface-to-surface missile was fired
on Thursday afternoon from a training range 130 kilometers away
from Brovary and it hit its target. 
