<HEADLINE> Chinese Companies Urged to Familiarize Themselves With Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua)-- Chinese companies must closely
watch the latest international development trends in business
management and be alert to the opportunities and challenges
brought about by Internet technology, said Chen Jinhua, vice
chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
Chen, also president of the Chinese Federation of Enterprises
and president of the China Entrepreneurs Association, said that
the Internet is making an enormous impact on traditional
management ideas and practices. E-commerce is also making a huge
impact on the economy.
</P>
<P>
Chen pointed out that Chinese companies should grasp resources
provided by the Internet and develop online marketing and e-
commerce.
</P>
<P>
"This is a issue that matters greatly to the future of Chinese
companies and company leaders must try their best to enter this
new field as soon as possible," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that with the globalization of the world economy
and China's entry into the WTO, Chinese companies must keep up
with international businesses. 
