Southeast Asia Nations (ASEAN) should further increase their
cooperation, said international studies experts participating in
the Seventh China-ASEAN Dialogue today.
</P>
<P>
Dao Shulin, an expert of South and Southeast Asia studies from
the China Institute of Contemporary International Relations, said
that strengthening cooperation between China and ASEAN enjoys a
solid foundation.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China and ASEAN countries share common interests
in maintaining peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific region and
developing their economies.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he said, China and ASEAN countries share similar
cultural background. The two sides have established close economic
relations, he said, adding that the two economies complement each
other to a large extent.
</P>
<P>
China and ASEAN have established many channels for exchange and
contact, such as high-level visits, regular meetings of foreign
ministers, regular consultations between high-level officials,
working groups for economic, trade and technological cooperation,
and numerous seminars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000421.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China and ASEAN Should Increase Cooperation: Experts (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dao said that China and ASEAN should further enhance
cooperation on political and security affairs, and join efforts in
keeping stability and peace in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The two sides should also strengthen economic and technological
cooperation, he noted, adding that the key areas include
establishing and maintaining a prevention mechanism for financial
safety, alleviating population problems and solving environmental
pollution.
</P>
<P>
Jusuf Wanandi, a senior researcher from the Center for
Strategic and International Studies of Indonesia, said that the
ASEAN and China should do exchange in more dialogue and
cooperation to strengthen mutual understanding and mutual trust.
</P>
<P>
The strengthening of cooperation between ASEAN and China is of
vital significance to the maintenance of peace and stability in
the region, Wanandi noted.
</P>
<P>
Other participants also elaborated the necessity of
strengthening cooperation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
China-ASEAN Dialogue is a non-governmental forum attended by
famous scholars and experts from China and the ASEAN countries.
The Dialogue is regularly co-sponsored by the China Institute of
Contemporary International Relations and the Institute of
Strategic and International Studies of ASEAN. 
</P>
</TEXT>
