<HEADLINE> Hezbollah Member Killed in Israeli Raids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Israel continued its attacks Friday
morning in south Lebanon and one Hezbollah guerrilla was killed in
the air raids, People's Sound radio station reported.
</P>
<P>
The radio reported that Israel warplanes launched four missiles
at the region near Nabatiye, bombing several villages. One bomb
fell on a market of Nabatiye but did not go off.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah admitted that one of its member was killed in Israel's
attacks on south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Fire tradings between Israel and resistance guerrillas
intensified after Israel formally notified the United Nations that
it would pull out its troops from south Lebanon by July.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak stressed Wednesday that his
country will retaliate if the resistance forces continue firing
Katyushas on north Israel or causes any casualties after its
withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel has occupied parts of south Lebanon since 1978. It set up
the present "security zone" in 1985, saying it needed to protect
its northern settlements from cross-border guerrilla attacks.
</P>
<P>
Syrian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has since been leading
a war of attrition to try to end the Israeli occupation of south
Lebanon.  
</P>
</TEXT>
