<HEADLINE> Militants Blow Up Electric Towers in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Militants blew up two electric
towers in Rajouri district in southwest Kashmir and disrupted the
local power supply late Thursday night, the Press Trust of India (
PTI) reported from Jammu and Kashmir Friday.
</P>
<P>
The two powerful improvised explosive devices attached to two
electric towers on the outskirts of Rajouri went off at around 11:
45 p.m. on Thursday, the PTI quoted local official sources as
saying, adding that no casualty was reported.
</P>
<P>
The blasts took place when local security forces engaged in
flushing out militants came close to a militant hideout, and the
militants escaped under the cover of the explosion, the PTI
reported. 
