<HEADLINE> Narcotics Recovered Near Rawalpindi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Anti-Narcotics Force
(ANF) has recovered and seized five kilograms of heroin, two
kilograms of opium and 20 kilograms of charas near Mulla Mansoor
west of Rawalpindi, a press release from the Regional Director of
ANF Rawalpindi said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
ANF took the action after the Regional Director of ANF
Rawalpindi had received a tip that an international gang was
operating in Northwest Frontier province and Punjab province and a
big quantity of narcotics would be smuggled into Punjab for onward
dispatch to some Gulf countries.
</P>
<P>
On receipt of this information, a raiding team was formed. The
team in a blockade at the highway near Mulla Mansoor stopped a
Toyota Corolla car coming from Peshawar. During a search, the
drugs were recovered from the secret cavities made in the car. Two
persons were arrested on the spot and the vehicle impounded.
</P>
