<HEADLINE> 24 People Killed in Plane Crash in Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Twenty Rwandan soldiers were
confirmed dead in a plane crash at Pepa, in Shaba Province of the
Democratic Republic of the Congo on Wednesday, Rwanda News Agency
reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The agency has learnt from the Rwandan army spokesman, Major
Emmanuel Ndahiro that one major, two captains, two lieutenants
plus 15 other soldiers died together with a crew of four who are
believed to be Russians.
</P>
<P>
The plane, an Antonov-8, was flying from Pepa heading for
Kigali. Soon after the plane took off, a crow ran into one of the
engines. The aircraft failed to continue on one engine and
exploded into flames on crash landing, Ndahiro explained.
</P>
<P>
"On knowing it, we sent a team of Russians to investigate the
cause of the crash, who found a carcass of a crow in one of the
engines. There are no survivors," Ndahiro said, adding that the
bodies have been brought back and burial arrangements are under
way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
