<HEADLINE> Four Central Asian States to Jointly Fight Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Four central Asian countries have
agreed to join hands to combat terrorism, political and religious
extremism, transnational organized crime and other threats to
regional security and stability.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state of Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan, Kyrgyzstan and
Tajikistan on Friday signed a treaty in this regard in the Uzbek
capital Tashkent, Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
