<HEADLINE> Russian Duma Ratifies Nuclear Test Ban Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma (lower house
of parliament) Friday overwhelmingly ratified the nuclear
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT).
</P>
<P>
The treaty passed the house with a vote of 298-74 with three
abstentions.
</P>
<P>
The ratification of the CTBT came one week after the Duma
approved the START II nuclear arms reduction pact with the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The United States, who has the world's largest and most
advanced nuclear arsenal, has not approved the global CTBT. The U.
S. Senate rejected the treaty in late 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
