<HEADLINE> Beijing Police Crack Down on Pickpockets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing police have launched a
battle against pickpockets on the city's buses in an effort to
create a safer travel environment for residents during the
upcoming seven holidays for International Labor Day.
</P>
<P>
A source from the public transport branch of the Beijing Public
Security Bureau said that some 70 pickpockets were nabbed by
police on buses yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The anti-pickpockets campaign started on the No. 300 bus line,
where pickpockets were frequently reported, the source said.
</P>
<P>
All buses in the Chinese capital are now under close police
supervision. 
