<HEADLINE> Mauritania Welcomes Chinese Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guangzhou, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Minister of Commerce,
Handicrafts and Tourism of Mauritania Ahamdy Ould Hamady today
welcomed Chinese enterprises to invest in Mauritania and promised
that his country will provide preferential policies.
</P>
<P>
Hamady made the remarks during the Sino-Mauritanian economic
and trade seminar held today at the ongoing China's Export
Commodities Fair.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have successfully cooperated in the fields of
agriculture, water conservancy and energy since they formed
diplomatic ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have to date signed 32 projects for trade and
economic cooperation with a total 900 million yuan, and China has
become Mauritania's most important trade partner, according to
Hamady.
</P>
<P>
Chinese enterprises are particularly encouraged to invest in
Mauritania's fur industry, agriculture, fishery and insurance
sectors, he said, adding that the two countries can benefit each
other as China possesses advanced technology and experience in
these areas. 
</P>
