<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice President Meets Gabonese Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice President Hu Jintao
said here today that China is ready to explore new ways of
cooperation in new areas with Gabon to further push forward Sino-
Gabonese friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark during a meeting with Jean Ping, minister of
State and minister of Foreign Affairs, Cooperation and French
Countries of Gabon. The Gabonese minister arrived here Thursday
morning for a week-long official visit.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that China appreciates the Gabonese Government's stance
on its relationship with China, its pursuit of the one-China
policy and support for China's reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
In the 26 years since the two countries established diplomatic
relations, the two countries have conducted fruitful cooperation
in areas of politics, economy, trade and culture. They have also
had close cooperation in many international affairs, noted Hu.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice president also expressed appreciation for the
Gabonese Government's efforts in promoting national stability,
unity among its ethnic groups, and economic recovery as well as
regional unity, cooperation and development in the country.
</P>
<P>
Jean Ping said that his country places high value on its
relationship with China, and is thankful for China's long-term
assistance. He pledged that Gabon will continue to stick to the
one-China policy, and will work together with China to expand
cooperation in various areas.
</P>
<P>
He said he appreciates China's proposal to hold a ministerial-
level China-Africa Cooperation Forum in Beijing, and wishes the
forum success.
</P>
<P>
The Gabonese minister is here at the invitation of Chinese
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan. He is scheduled to stay in China
until April 26.  
</P>
</TEXT>
