<HEADLINE> CMC Vice-Chairman Meets Czech Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The one-China principle is the
premise of peaceful reunification with Taiwan, the Taiwan issue
cannot drag on indefinitely, and no form of "Taiwan independence"
will be tolerated, a vice-chairman of China's Central Military
Commission said today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wannian made the remarks when meeting Jaromir Novotny,
the first deputy minister of the Czech Republic defense ministry.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that the reunification of the motherland is favored
by the majority of the people and is the general trend. Any
attempt to create independence for Taiwan will be opposed by all
Chinese -- including the people of Taiwan -- and is doomed to fail,
he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Zhang expressed his appreciation for the Czech government's one-
China stance.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese government has maintained the long-term,
friendly relations with the Czechs, and voiced his hope that the
military and state relations between the two countries would
develop further on the basis of mutual respect, mutual benefit and
non-interference in each other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Novotny said that the Czech government and army have adhered to
the one-China stance and never developed official relations with
Taiwan. He said he hopes that Czech-China cooperative relations
will continue to thrive.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the General Staff of the People
's Liberation Army, attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
