army has set up an award for military technicians in a bid to
improve competence in battle.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Central Military Commission said that it
is the first such award ever offered in the Chinese army, and is
expected to help modernization of the armed forces and encourage
military technicians to contribute to national defense.
</P>
<P>
Today's Liberation Army Daily reported that the award will go
to military technicians who have made major technical innovations,
solved ongoing technical problems, helped achieve military,
economic and social benefits, and played important roles in
carrying out the mission of the military.
</P>
<P>
The award will be given every three years, said the paper.
