<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia in Efforts to Develop Capital Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia is serious in its
efforts to develop its capital market and measures are being taken
to ensure that it advances in a structured and prudent manner,
Finance Ministry Adviser Mustapa Mohamad said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mustapa said Malaysia has all the components needed for its
capital markets to flourish and all that is required to move
forward is the experience, maturity of market players,
sophisticated products, high discipline and professionalism.
</P>
<P>
After years of promoting, introducing and improving, Malaysia
can be proud that it now has a whole range of exchanges to cater
for all types of trading along with the peripheral support
activities, he told an international seminar here.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia now boasts four exchanges -- the Kuala Lumpur Stock
Exchange, Kuala Lumpur Options and Financial Futures Exchange,
Commodities and Monetary Exchange and Malaysian Exchange of
Securities Dealing and Automated Quotation Stock, Mustapa said.
</P>
<P>
He said that as shareholders as a whole are getting smarter,
companies may now be forced to source financing directly from the
capital markets.
</P>
<P>
As for the local unit trust industry, efforts to
institutionalize the market would ultimately lead to stability in
the market when the volatility of share price movements decreased,
he said.
</P>
<P>
As the fund management and unit trust industry grows, the
market exposure of institutional investors will increase, thus
ensuring the Malaysian market would continue to develop and mature
in a stable environment, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
