<HEADLINE> Child Abuse Cases Rises in Thailand: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 21 (Xinhua) -- About 120 Thai children have been
found sexually abused last year, almost doubling the 1998 figure,
The Center for the Protection of the Children's Rights said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The center said in a report that the rise in the number of
child abuse cases was alarming. In 1998, only 75 Thai children
were found to be the victims of sexual abuse, it said.
</P>
<P>
Center head Sanpasit attributed family neglect as a major cause
for the children's suffering.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the organization had helped some 4,000
children since 1981 and all of them were victims of such neglect.
</P>
<P>
Sanpasit said that most of the parents of the victims did not
intend to neglect their children but they did not know how to take
care of them.
</P>
<P>
"Children's fates lie in their family's hands," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
