<HEADLINE> Ugandan Vice President to Attend New Rwandan President's Swearing-in Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan Vice President Speciosa
Kazibwe will attend on Saturday the swearing-in ceremony of Paul
Kagame, the newly- elected president of Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
"President Yoweri Museveni is unable to attend the ceremony,"
Hope Kivengere, secretary of Ugandan President, told Xinhua in a
telephone interview. "He has left here today for a mini-summit in
Zimbabwe to discuss the war in the Democratic Republic of the
Congo," she added.
</P>
<P>
The vice president will lead a government delegation to Kigali,
which includes National Political Commissar James Wapakhabulo and
Chairman of the Parliamentary Committee on Presidential Affairs
Elly Karuhanga.
</P>
<P>
Kagame was elected president by Rwandan parliamentarians and
ministers on April 17, replacing Pasteur Bizimungu who resigned
last month. Kagame is the first Tutsi president in the
land-locked Hutu-dominant central African country since its
independence in 1962. 
</P>
