<HEADLINE> hke042114-- 80 Hospitalized for Suspected Food Poisoning in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Some 80 people, 54 of them
children, fell sick and were hospitalized Thursday after consuming
ice candies in a village in Kathua district of Jammu, local police
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The children, on their way home from school, and 26 adults took
the ice candies at Charra village, according to the Press Trust of
India.
</P>
<P>
They soon started complaining of stomach disorders and were
rushed to a nearby hospital where the conditions of some of them
were described as serious. Some had even lost consciousness.
</P>
<P>
A search is on to trace the ice-candy seller. 
</P>
