<HEADLINE> Italian Ruling Coalition Names Amato as Candidate for Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Italian ruling center-left coalition
on Friday morning named current Treasury Minister Gulio Amato as
candidate for prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The nomination was announced by the ruling Left Democratic
Party's parliamentary leader Fabio Mussi, after his meeting with
Italian President Carlo Azeglio Ciampi Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Ciampi met with leaders of parties to open the second round of
consultations aimed at naming a premier-designate to replace the
outgoing government leader, Massimo D'Alema, who resigned on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The opposition Freedom Front leaders, who are pushing for an
immediate general election, have come out strongly against Amato.
</P>
<P>
They have also hinted that Amato does not have the
parliamentary backing as the left thinks he does.
</P>
<P>
Amato returned at dawn from the spring session of the
International Monetary Fund in New York Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
After 18 months at the helm of his center-left coalition,
D'Alema handed the president his resignation in the wake of heavy
center-left losses in regional elections held last Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
