<HEADLINE> Jubilo Enters Final of Asian Club Soccer Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Jubilo Iwata of Japan was on its
way to retain the Asian club championship with a 2-0 semifinal win
over Iran's Pirouzi Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Naohiro Takahara and Masashi Nakayama scored the goals in the
second half, enabling their team into Saturday's final against Al
Hilal of Saudi Arabia who beat Suwon Bluewings of South Korea 1-0.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Sergio Ricardo scored a controversial winner after
just 11 minutes as his goal looked offside and later confirmed by
television replays.
</P>
<P>
However, the South Koreans were still kept away from the
championship match.
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal against the Iranian champions, Jubilo
squandered numerous opportunities before Takahara broke the
deadlock in the 67th minute.
</P>
<P>
Nakayama sealed the game against Pirouzi with the last kick of
the match. 
</P>
