<DOCNO> XIE20000421.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CMC Vice-Chairman Meets Australian Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Wannian, Vice-Chairman of
China's Central Military Commission, reiterated here today that
China never allows any form of "Taiwan independence," foreign
interference in the Taiwan issue, nor letting the Taiwan issue
remain unsettled without time limit.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, in a meeting with visiting Chief Commander of the
Australian Defense Forces Chris Barrie, stressed that China
persists in the policy of "peaceful reunification" and "one China,
two systems," but will not commit to abandoning the use of force
if necessary.
</P>
<P>
The principle of "one China" is the basis and precondition for
peacefully resolving the Taiwan issue, he said, adding that the
Chinese People's Liberation Army, with determination and
confidence, has the ability to realized the complete reunification
of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Barrie said Australia will hold firmly to the "one China"
principle.
</P>
<P>
Zhang expressed his satisfaction that the relations between the
two armed forces are in the best period of their history as the
two countries have been committing themselves to the long-term,
steady and healthy development of their all-around cooperative
relations.
</P>
<P>
he said he hopes that both armed forces will further cooperate
to contribute to the peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Barrie agreed that military ties are an important component of
bilateral relations and suggested cooperation and exchange between
both armed forces be enhanced, particularly between young officers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000421.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Cities Report Unhealthy Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During April 14-20, Lanzhou and Hohhot reported hazardous air
and Zhengzhou, Yinchuan, Xining and Xi'an reported poor air.
</P>
<P>
Eight cities, including Tianjin, Beijing, Xining, Shijiazhuang,
Yinchuan, Hohhot and Taiyuan reported hazardous air, while
Zhengzhou and Lanzhou reported poor air during the previous week.
</P>
<P>
Shijiazhuang, Taiyuan, Beijing, Tianjin, Changchun, Urumqi,
Chongqing and Harbin reported slight air pollution during this
week.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six cities, including Shenyang, Shanghai, Changsha,
Hangzhou, Chengdu, enjoyed fairly good air, while Ningbo, Haikou,
Zhanjiang, Shenzhen, Xiamen and Beihai reported excellent air.
</P>
<P>
Lanzhou, Hohhot and Zhengzhou and other 34 cities listed
suspended particles as the major pollutant. Sulfur dioxide was the
major pollutant in Chongqing, Changsha and Nantong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
