<HEADLINE> Malaria Kills 121 People in Southwest Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The dreaded highland malaria has
claimed 121 lives in southwest Kenya's Kissi District this year,
the East African Standard reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
About 12,128 people were diagnosed to be affected by the
epidemic in the area, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
However, Nyanza provincial officials denied that the situation
was deteriorating, saying that the efforts were under way to
prevent a large- scale disease outbreak.
</P>
<P>
About three weeks ago, the Kenyan government sounded out a
malaria alert for parts of Nyanza and Rift Valley provinces.
</P>
<P>
Malaria, one of the top killers in Africa, is a mosquito-borne
tropical endemic. So far there is no vaccine for the disease, but
international scientists believe that a small amount of money can
prevent the deaths from the disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
