<HEADLINE> Barak, Abdullah to Meet on Bilateral, Regional Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud
Barak is to hold talks with Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein on
Sunday in Israel's southern resort city of Eilat, Prime Minister's
Office said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah is scheduled to arrive at an Israeli naval base in
Eilat by boat Sunday morning from Akaba, Jordan's southern resort
city just opposite Eilat, and Barak will meet the king there, the
office added.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will visit a local Israeli factory before
sitting down for a working meeting at a hotel in the city to
discuss specific bilateral economic cooperation and the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Barak will be joined at the meeting by Regional Cooperation
Minister Shimon Peres, Foreign Minister David Levy, Environment
Mminister Dalia Itzik and Industry and Trade Minister Ran Cohen.
</P>
<P>
Barak will head down to Eilat Friday with his family members for
a long weekend of rest and relaxation.
</P>
<P>
The office said that Abdullah will return to Jordan on the same
day. 
</P>
