<HEADLINE> Australia Forgives Poor Countries Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Australian Foreign Minister
Alexander Downer said here Friday that Australia would forgive all
10.71 million U.S. dollars of debts owed by Nicaragua and Ethiopia,
Australian Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
It was an answer to a World Bank/International Monetary Fund
initiative, Downer said.
</P>
<P>
of the 40 third world countries identified for relief, only the
two owed debts to Australia, separately 3.39 million and 7.497
million dollars, related mainly to machinery supplied by private
sector firms.
</P>
<P>
Explaining why the bilateral debt Australia is owed is
considerably less than the major industrial economies, Downer and
Treasurer Peter Costello said Australia had only a small
proportion of debt owed by poorer countries, because the
government mainly supplied funds to the Third World in the form of
grants.
</P>
<P>
The Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD)
ranked last December Australia at the low end of the organization'
s list of aid donor nations.
</P>
<P>
According to the OECD, the percentage of Australian GNP devoted
to aid dropped to 0.27 percent and this is well below the United
Nation's target of 0.7 percent and also below the OECD average of
0.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
