<HEADLINE> hke042112--Musharraf Announces Human Rights Framework in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Chief Executive
General Pervez Musharraf Friday articulated a framework on human
rights that will help Pakistan eliminate injustice, strive for the
establishment of a moral order, ensure freedom for the people and
promote tolerance and harmony in society.
</P>
<P>
"The government attaches a high priority to human rights and
the government will take bold steps to protect and promote human
rights," Musharraf said at the Convention on Human Rights and
Human Dignity.
</P>
<P>
The framework, he said, envisages the need to eliminate
injustice and poverty, safeguard human dignity and human rights,
establish the rule of law and a moral order, ensure freedom to
people to enable them to be the masters of their destiny, achieve
a balance between rights and responsibilities of a citizen and
promote tolerance and harmony in the society.
</P>
<P>
Musharraf said his government believes in equality and justice
as enshrined in the ideals of Islam and which are also mirrored in
the U.N. Human Rights Declaration.
</P>
<P>
"Our government will endeavor to create an environment to allow
each Pakistani to lead his life with dignity and respect," he said.
</P>
