<HEADLINE> Number of South Korean Internet Users Up 900,000 Monthly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The number of Internet users in
South Korea rose by 900,000 every month since last October,
hitting 13.9 million at the end of last month.
</P>
<P>
Users in the 20s age bracket took the largest share with 5
million, followed by 4.78 million users aged 7-19 and 2.59 million
in the 30s. A total of 92.2 percent of university students used
the Web, said Korea Network Information Center said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Of Internet users who used the Web at least once a month, men
numbered 8.7 million and women 5.2 million, according to a 8,500-
people survey by the center.
</P>
<P>
Some 30.6 percent used Internet 4-10 hours a week and average
use was 6.7 hours, up 2.2 hours from a survey in last October.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 61.9 percent said they use the Internet to search
for information, 19.5 percent for games and entertainment, 10.9
percent for chatting and 6.8 percent for e-mail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
