<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Mark World Asthma Day in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will host a week-long
medical information drive to mark World Asthma Day, which falls on
May 3.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the day is "Helping All People Breathe normally",
and the campaign will include a seminar about the care of asthma
patients, an open-air fair providing consultations on asthma
control, and a medical training program on treating asthma.
</P>
<P>
The city established an asthma control society in 1992 which
now has more than 4,000 members, including 1,000 doctors and 3,000
patients.
</P>
<P>
About 150 million people worldwide suffer from asthma, a common
lung disease characterized by breathing problems.
</P>
<P>
There are 500,000 asthma sufferers in China, 2.5 percent of
whom are below the age of 14.
</P>
<P>
Many people are stuck with asthma because they do not insist on
proper treatment, and therefore fail to find a complete cure. But
experts say the disease can be controlled with proper treatment.
</P>
</TEXT>
