<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Rising In Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province ratified the
establishment of 317 overseas-funded enterprises during the first
quarter this year, involving nearly 536 million US dollars of
contractual overseas investment, up 36.6 percent from a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Of all the investment sources, Hong Kong ranked the first,
followed by the U.S., Taiwan Province, Japan, and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Of the total contractual overseas investment introduced during
the quarter, some 76.4 percent was for local industrial projects,
while the amount put into the real estate sector was 22 times that
of the same period in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of wholly owned foreign enterprises used more
than half of the total contractual overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
By the end of March, the number of overseas-funded enterprises
in the province had reached 17,014, involving 22.48 billion US
dollars of contractual investment. This number includes 883
enterprises that each invested more than 10 million US dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
