<DOCNO> XIE20000421.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Enhances Sewage Disposal to Curb Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province is making efforts to build sewage processing plants in
order to reduce the pollution of the rivers and the sea.
</P>
<P>
Du Qiugen, director of the Liaoning Provincial Environmental
Protection Bureau, said the province has planned 12 sewage
disposal plants, including three which have been completed, three
under construction, and six to be built.
</P>
<P>
The three sewage plants, completed in northern and southern
Shenyang, capital of Liaoning Province, and in the city of Anshan
City, are now in trial operation.
</P>
<P>
According to Du, the designed daily sewage disposal capacity of
the 12 sewage plants in the eight cities is 2.8 million tons,
accounting for 75 percent of the total sewage daily discharged
there.
</P>
<P>
As an industrial base, Liaoning has a heavy task in curbing
pollution. The Liaohe River, running through eight cities in
Liaoning, has been seriously polluted by sewage discharged by the
cities.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Liaoning allocated seven million yuan for
preparation work on the construction of the sewage plants, and
plans to get more than 300 million yuan from state bond for their
construction.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this year, Liaoning will begin the construction
of seven other sewage disposal projects aimed at processing more
than 60 percent of the sewage now discharged into the Liaohe River.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
