<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Determined To Crack Down on Shoddy Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province has determined
to focus its efforts and forces on cracking down on cases involved
in the production and sale of shoddy and inferior products over
the next two months, according to provincial Vice Governor Ye
Rongbao.
</P>
<P>
Serious quality problems are still to be found in local
township and private enterprises and at some local markets, Ye
said, and the province intends to intensify law enforcement and
strike out against these phony products.
</P>
<P>
An examination by the State Bureau of Quality and Technical
Supervision revealed that Zhejiang's product quality was worse
than the national average every year beginning in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Last year Zhejiang province resolved 66,000 cases involving 650
million yuan worth of fake and shoddy products, and destroyed more
than 4,000 production and marketing locations. 
