<DOCNO> XIE20000421.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Bright Spots Appears in China's FDI (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- New bright spots have appeared in
China's use of foreign direct investments (FDI), according to the
latest issue of Outlook, the country's most authoritative news
weekly.
</P>
<P>
The April 24 issue of the magazine said that over the past two
years, foreign direct investments in China have been on a decline
because of changes in the domestic economy and the lingering
impact of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, foreign direct investment in China stood at 40.4
billion U.S. dollars, down 11.4 percent from the previous year,
the first negative growth of FDI in China for several years.
</P>
<P>
However, changes now have taken place in both China and the
world. In China, the pace of entry into the World Trade
Organization (WTO) has quickened, and the strategy of developing
the vast western region is underway.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the global economy is witnessing a noticeable
recovery trend, and U.S. and European investors have begun once
again to show keen interest in investing in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Against this backdrop, "new bright spots" have appeared in
China's use of FDI, which has also entered into a new phase of
development, the magazine said.
</P>
<P>
One of the bright spots is large multinationals increasing
their investment in China, according to the news weekly.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000421.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Bright Spots Appears in China's FDI (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Statistics show that to date more than 400 of the world's 500
biggest multinationals are operating in China, engaged in
businesses ranging from machinery, electronics, chemicals, and
building materials to telecommunications, medicine, and food.
</P>
<P>
Before deciding to invest in China, multinationals usually make
a thorough investigation of the local investment environment. Once
decided, they sweep in and try to occupy as much of the market as
possible, and are disinclined to withdraw when minor changes occur
in the country, the magazine said.
</P>
<P>
Many multinationals have also moved their overseas headquarters
to China, and currently, China hosts over 100 multinational
regional headquarters.
</P>
<P>
One of these is Alcatel SA of France, which moved its Asia-
Pacific headquarters to Shanghai early this year. The
telecommunications equipment supplier now has 17 joint ventures
and 4 wholly owned businesses in China.
</P>
<P>
Also, Chinese companies have showed an enthusiasm to list on
overseas markets, especially those companies related to the new
information economy. China.dom.com, Netease, Sohu, Homeway, and
8848 all have been listed or are preparing to be listed on the U.S.
's NASDAQ, the magazine said.
</P>
<P>
And many domestic companies are or are about to be listed in
the growth enterprises market in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The magazine noted that the Chinese government should remain
aware of the general trend of FDI in the country and take measures
that will best benefit the overall economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000421.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guizhou Opens Four New Tourist Routes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guizhou
Province will open new scenic spots in four directions with
Guiyang, the provincial capital, as the center.
</P>
<P>
The eastern route comprises of 10 sites featuring ethnic tastes.
The western route is featured by karst caves. The southern route
covers virgin forest and villages inhabited by Puyi, Yao and Shui
nationalities.
</P>
<P>
The northern route is dotted with buildings and museums in
memory of the Long March conducted by the Red Army led by the
Chinese Communist Party during the 1934-36 period.
</P>
<P>
Chishui City, which is well-known both at home and abroad for
Chishui River War where the Red Army traversed four times to and
fro, has turned into a new tourist attraction. It has built a
state-level forest park and will build a dinosaur park.
</P>
<P>
In addition, these tourist sites are connected with famous
cities in other provinces such as Kunming, capital of Yunnan
province, Zhangjiajie, in Hunan province, Guilin, in Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, and the Three Gorges in Hubei province.
</P>
<P>
Guizhou has more than 1,000 historical and scenic spots, 200 of
which have been opened to visitors. The province played host to 5.
3 million domestic tourists and 167,000 overseas visitors in 1999,
netting a combined tourism revenue of 4.8 billion yuan (578
million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
