<HEADLINE> Mexico Police Seizes Drug Smuggler Suspect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 20 (Xinhua) -- A drug smuggler suspect has
been caught and detained by the Mexican Federal Judicial Police
agents during an operation carried out in the Rio Bravo
municipality in Tamaulipas state, the authorities said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Villanueva Izaguirre, federal police deputy in
Tamaulipas, told the press that the operation began on Wednesday
night in the Rio Bravo municipality.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hugo Cruz Hernandez, 27, was detained when he was
driving a pickup truck with U.S. license plate. The agents found
86 packages containing 10 kilograms each and two bags with 47 one-
kilogram packages in the cabin of the truck.
</P>
<P>
The federal police official said that the drug, the driver and
the vehicle have been put under the custody of the Federal Public
Attorney Office.  
</P>
