<HEADLINE> IDB to Grant 200 Million Dollars to Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) has agreed to grant Panama 200 million U.S.
dollars to clean the Panama Bay, Panamanian Second Vice President
Dominador Kaizer said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kaizer regarded the investment as "positive", saying it will
facilitate the rehabilitation of the commercial area urgently
needed in the bay zone.
</P>
<P>
The cleaning work could start by the end of this year and would
take some 10 years to be completed, said Kaizer. But he did not
say when the IDB credit would be signed. 
