NAIROBI -- Jean Bosco Barayagwiza, a key genocide suspect, has
refused to plead guilty or not guilty to the charges brought
against him by the prosecutor at the International Criminal
Tribunal for Rwanda (ICTR) based in the northern Tanzanian town of
Arusha.
</P>
<P>
According to Rwanda News Agency on Thursday, Barayagwiza,
former director of political affairs in Rwandan foreign ministry
and one of the founders of the extremist Radio Television Libre
des Mille Collines (RTLM), was accused of genocide, crimes against
humanity and serious violation of the Geneva Conventions. (BC-
Rwanda-Genocide)
