KHARTOUM-- The U.S. Embassy in Khartoum resumed its function
with the arrival of Charge D'Affaires Donald Titlbom here from
Nairobi last Saturday after a two-year suspension, the Sudanese
News Agency (SNA) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Consul Donald Mulligan will arrive here from Cairo early
next week and an administrative attache is due to arrive here from
Nairobi, capital of Kenya, soon, SNA added. (BC-Sudan-U.S.)
</P>
