<HEADLINE> Beijing Reports Fast Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The gross domestic product (GDP)
of the Chinese capital increased ten percent on a yearly basis to
44.91 billion yuan in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the city's industrial enterprises
achieved 14.35 billion yuan in added value in the three-month
period, up 14.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Beijing also invested 11.31 billion yuan in fixed assets, up 13
percent. A total of 700,000 square meters of houses were sold out,
up 170 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, Beijing imported and exported 6.15
billion US dollars of goods in the first quater of this year, up
57 percent.
</P>
<P>
And 213 new foreign-funded enterprises were set up, involving
550 million US dollars in contractual foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The city played host to 459,000 foreign tourists in the three-
month period, up 14.6 percent. 
</P>
