<HEADLINE> Cole's Euro 2000 Dream Shattered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 20 (Xinhua) -- West Ham star Joe Cole has
fractured his right leg - ending his hopes of a place in England's
Euro 2000 squad.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old was at first thought to have suffered just bad
bruising after a challenge in the Hammers' 2-1 win at Derby on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But Cole has been in pain since and was sent for a further scan
which indicated the fracture.
</P>
<P>
The news ends England coach Kevin Keegan's hopes that Cole
would break into the senior squad in time for June's European
championships. He had already been selected for Under-21 duty.
</P>
<P>
West Ham boss Harry Redknapp said: "I'm sorry to say Euro 2000
is now out of the window for him - this is a terrible blow for Joe
and the club. No one wants to lose a huge talent like his.
</P>
<P>
"We all feel for young Joe and I can assure you we will do all
we can to look after him until he is on his feet again and back in
action. But he is only 18 and there will be plenty more
championships for him to get involved in as an England player," he
said. 
</P>
