Sukur's curling effort just before the break kept Leeds on the
back-foot in a game which also saw Harry Kewell and Emre Belozoglu
sent-off.
</P>
<P>
Following the death of two Leeds fans in fighting before the
first leg, Thursday's game had the biggest police presence of any
match in English soccer history but, apart from some pre-match
skirmishes between home fans and police, it passed off without any
major crowd trouble. 
