<HEADLINE> British Police Helicopter Crashes in Cardiff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A British police helicopter Friday
crash landed on a house in a residential area of Cardiff, the
capital city of Welse.
</P>
<P>
A BBC report quoted witnesses as saying that they heard the
noise of the aircraft's engine and then saw it "park on a roof,"
at Coryton Crescent, Whitchurch, north Cardiff.
</P>
<P>
It had hovered above the houses for about 10 minutes when
something appeared to go wrong with the rotor blades.
</P>
<P>
The engine stopped and it fell from the sky into a semi-
detached house, witnesses added.
</P>
<P>
No one has been killed, and no one has so far been reported as
seriously injured in the incident which South Wales Police said
happened at about 1920 GMT.
</P>
<P>
The occupants of one half of the semi-detached house are away
while the other neighbors escaped from their house unhurt but
shaken.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter crew are also not believed to have been
seriously hurt. 
</P>
