<HEADLINE> Cuba Sugar Output Surpasses Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Cuban authorities announced Friday
that the present sugar cane harvest will be 4 million tons
compared with 3.7 million tons in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Sugar Ministry delegate Alfredo Hondal said that the quality of
the sugar obtained from the present harvest surpasses the levels
agreed on in the export contracts.
</P>
<P>
Hondal explained that the losses of the firms of services and
support to the harvest in the previous season amounted to 100
million pesos (the same figure in dollars at the official rate of
exchange), while now they are reduced to zero.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimated that the current Cuban sugar output could
reach 4 million tons, reflecting the recovery of that industry,
but it is still far from the record 9 million tons obtained
several years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
