<HEADLINE> Mexicans in U.S. To Send Home 6 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Mexico will receive this year
some 6 billion dollars from its nationals residing in the United
States, and 85 percent of these resources will be used for food
expenses by their families, said the Economic Commission for Latin
America and the Caribbean (CEPAL) Friday.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala, El Salvador, Honduras and Nicaragua will receive
from their nationals in the United States between 2.5 billion
dollars to 3 billion dollars from remittances, according to the
CEPAL estimates, published Friday in the press.
</P>
<P>
El Salvador will receive half of that amount, and with this the
importance of the economic and political life in that country.
</P>
<P>
Central Americans send money to help their families, but
without neglecting the development of their communities, through
the associations of Central American migrants in the United States.
</P>
</TEXT>
